definition: to change or replace/to experience/one of the five two-hour periods into which the night was formerly divided/watch (e.g. of a sentry or guard)
(of sth) to move/to set in movement/to displace/to touch/to make use of/to stir (emotions)/to alter/abbr. for 動詞|动词[dong4 ci2], verb

sentences.english: The order of the earlier chapters were altered.
sentences.chinese: 前几章的次序被更动了。

sentences.english: As always, if we over-compensated, we'll adjust the numbers again. But as I said, our initial round of nerfs wasn't sufficient.
sentences.chinese: 经常，假若我们偏激了，我们会再一次更动这些数字。

sentences.english: I want to make a change in your plan .
sentences.chinese: 我想对你的计划做点更动。

sentences.english: New species and taxonomic changes in Ardisia Swartz from China.
sentences.chinese: 中国紫金牛属新种和分类上的更动。

sentences.english: Do not change the form randomly.
sentences.chinese: 请勿任意增删列，更动格式。

sentences.english: All prices are subject to change without notice.
sentences.chinese: 所有的报价随时会更动，恕不另行通知。

sentences.english: You are not authorized to reparent or change subtopics links on this ZWiki Page.
sentences.chinese: 您没有权力在这页更动父页或子主题连结。

sentences.english: Many customs associated with Spring Festival have changed, too.
sentences.chinese: 与春节相关的许多民俗也被更动了。

sentences.english: If you swap hardware or need to detect/re-detect hardware this can be left enabled .
sentences.chinese: 如果更换硬件或需要探测硬件更动，开启它。

sentences.english: Do not make any other changes to the disks while waiting for your configurations to take effect.
sentences.chinese: 在等待磁碟设置生效之前，请不要更动你的磁碟。

sentences.english: I want to make a change in your plan.
sentences.chinese: 我想对你的计划做点儿更动。

sentences.english: If we plan far enough in advance, we will have plenty of time to make changes.
sentences.chinese: 如果我们很早就开始计画，就会有足够的时间做更动。

sentences.english: The testicular structure changes with season and total length of the shark.
sentences.chinese: 精巢的结构随体长和季节的更动而变化。
